{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":545,"text":"Two years ago, after having served four years"},{"time":2970,"text":"in the United States Marine Corps"},{"time":4630,"text":"and deployments to both Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":6990,"text":"I found myself in Port-au-Prince, leading a team"},{"time":9939,"text":"of veterans and medical professionals"},{"time":12176,"text":"in some of the hardest-hit areas of that city,"},{"time":14609,"text":"three days after the earthquake."},{"time":16135,"text":"We were going to the places that nobody else wanted to go,"},{"time":18298,"text":"the places nobody else could go, and after three weeks,"},{"time":21829,"text":"we realized something. Military veterans"},{"time":24835,"text":"are very, very good at disaster response."},{"time":27848,"text":"And coming home, my cofounder and I,"},{"time":30323,"text":"we looked at it, and we said, there are two problems."},{"time":33586,"text":"The first problem is there's inadequate disaster response."},{"time":36592,"text":"It's slow. It's antiquated. It's not using the best technology,"},{"time":39906,"text":"and it's not using the best people."},{"time":42287,"text":"The second problem that we became aware of"},{"time":44492,"text":"was a very inadequate veteran reintegration,"},{"time":46970,"text":"and this is a topic that is front page news right now"},{"time":49115,"text":"as veterans are coming home from Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":51276,"text":"and they're struggling to reintegrate into civilian life."},{"time":54426,"text":"And we sat here and we looked at these two problems,"},{"time":56306,"text":"and finally we came to a realization. These aren't problems."},{"time":59040,"text":"These are actually solutions. And what do I mean by that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62502,"text":"Well, we can use disaster response as an opportunity"},{"time":65572,"text":"for service for the veterans coming home."},{"time":67973,"text":"Recent surveys show that 92 percent of veterans want"},{"time":70473,"text":"to continue their service when they take off their uniform."},{"time":72713,"text":"And we can use veterans to improve disaster response."},{"time":76383,"text":"Now on the surface, this makes a lot of sense, and in 2010,"},{"time":79446,"text":"we responded to the tsunami in Chile,"},{"time":82455,"text":"the floods in Pakistan, we sent training teams to the Thai-Burma border."},{"time":86349,"text":"But it was earlier this year, when one of our"},{"time":88981,"text":"original members caused us to shift focus in the organization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93086,"text":"This is Clay Hunt. Clay was a Marine with me."},{"time":95831,"text":"We served together in Iraq and Afghanistan."},{"time":98157,"text":"Clay was with us in Port-au-Prince. He was also with us in Chile."},{"time":102091,"text":"Earlier this year, in March, Clay took his own life."},{"time":105977,"text":"This was a tragedy, but it really forced us"},{"time":108707,"text":"to refocus what it is that we were doing."},{"time":111985,"text":"You know, Clay didn't kill himself because of what happened"},{"time":115449,"text":"in Iraq and Afghanistan. Clay killed himself"},{"time":118057,"text":"because of what he lost when he came home."},{"time":121206,"text":"He lost purpose. He lost his community."},{"time":124671,"text":"And perhaps most tragically, he lost his self-worth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129106,"text":"And so, as we evaluated, and as the dust settled"},{"time":132280,"text":"from this tragedy, we realized that, of those two problems --"},{"time":136594,"text":"in the initial iteration of our organization,"},{"time":139834,"text":"we were a disaster response organization that was using"},{"time":142707,"text":"veteran service. We had a lot of success,"},{"time":144946,"text":"and we really felt like we were changing the disaster response paradigm."},{"time":149159,"text":"But after Clay, we shifted that focus, and suddenly,"},{"time":152568,"text":"now moving forward, we see ourselves"},{"time":155044,"text":"as a veteran service organization that's using disaster response."},{"time":159937,"text":"Because we think that we can give that purpose"},{"time":162547,"text":"and that community and that self-worth back to the veteran."},{"time":165728,"text":"And tornadoes in Tuscaloosa and Joplin, and then later"},{"time":167959,"text":"Hurricane Irene, gave us an opportunity to look at that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171660,"text":"Now I want you to imagine for a second an 18-year-old boy"},{"time":175069,"text":"who graduates from high school in Kansas City, Missouri."},{"time":177545,"text":"He joins the Army. The Army gives him a rifle."},{"time":180109,"text":"They send him to Iraq."},{"time":181781,"text":"Every day he leaves the wire with a mission."},{"time":184508,"text":"That mission is to defend the freedom of the family that he left at home."},{"time":188112,"text":"It's to keep the men around him alive."},{"time":190201,"text":"It's to pacify the village that he works in."},{"time":192387,"text":"He's got a purpose. But he comes home [to] Kansas City, Missouri,"},{"time":196051,"text":"maybe he goes to college, maybe he's got a job,"},{"time":198649,"text":"but he doesn't have that same sense of purpose."},{"time":201013,"text":"You give him a chainsaw. You send him to Joplin, Missouri"},{"time":203153,"text":"after a tornado, he regains that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205513,"text":"Going back, that same 18-year-old boy graduates from high school"},{"time":208562,"text":"in Kansas City, Missouri, joins the Army,"},{"time":210507,"text":"the Army gives him a rifle, they send him to Iraq."},{"time":213215,"text":"Every day he looks into the same sets of eyes around him."},{"time":216122,"text":"He leaves the wire. He knows that those people have his back."},{"time":219283,"text":"He's slept in the same sand. They've lived together."},{"time":221466,"text":"They've eaten together. They've bled together."},{"time":224165,"text":"He goes home to Kansas City, Missouri."},{"time":226563,"text":"He gets out of the military. He takes his uniform off."},{"time":229623,"text":"He doesn't have that community anymore."},{"time":230962,"text":"But you drop 25 of those veterans in Joplin, Missouri,"},{"time":234196,"text":"they get that sense of community back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":236687,"text":"Again, you have an 18-year-old boy who graduates"},{"time":239126,"text":"high school in Kansas City."},{"time":240782,"text":"He joins the Army. The Army gives him a rifle."},{"time":242498,"text":"They send him to Iraq."},{"time":244037,"text":"They pin a medal on his chest. He goes home to a ticker tape parade."},{"time":248392,"text":"He takes the uniform off. He's no longer Sergeant Jones"},{"time":250810,"text":"in his community. He's now Dave from Kansas City."},{"time":253423,"text":"He doesn't have that same self-worth."},{"time":255696,"text":"But you send him to Joplin after a tornado,"},{"time":258308,"text":"and somebody once again is walking up to him"},{"time":260128,"text":"and shaking their hand and thanking them for their service,"},{"time":262502,"text":"now they have self-worth again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264819,"text":"I think it's very important, because right now"},{"time":267140,"text":"somebody needs to step up,"},{"time":268903,"text":"and this generation of veterans has the opportunity"},{"time":270854,"text":"to do that if they are given the chance."},{"time":273139,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}